QuickJS / MicroQuickJS should be treated as a real engineering risk if it is anywhere in your stack. The grounded fact I can safely anchor on is CVE-2025-62495 tied to this runtime family. {{fact:ground_truth:MQUICKJS}}

What is environment-specific is whether you embed or inherit it directly or transitively. Treat exposure as unverified until you inventory services, binaries, images, SDKs, and vendored source. {{fact:ground_truth:MQUICKJS}}

Mitigation plan: inventory direct and transitive use, identify the exact version or vendored commit, isolate the highest-risk untrusted-input paths first, and keep containment in place until the patched upstream release is confirmed. {{fact:ground_truth:MQUICKJS}}

